• The Oedipus complex: This refers to the development of sexual feelings toward one's parent of the opposite sex, which can lead to feelings of guilt and conflict.

• The Electra complex: This refers to the development of sexual feelings toward one's father, which can lead to feelings of jealousy and rivalry.

• The Latent and manifest stages: These refer to the different stages of development that a person goes through in terms of their sexual feelings and behavior.

• The Sexual Revolution: This refers to a period in history where societal norms around sexuality began to change, leading to increased acceptance of various forms of sexual expression.

• Kinsey's scale: This is a continuum that measures a person's sexual orientation, ranging from exclusively heterosexual to exclusively homosexual.

• Kinsey's concept of "sexual identity": This refers to an individual's sense of self as it relates to their sexual orientation.

• Gender identity: This refers to an individual's sense of self as it relates to their gender identity (e.g., male, female, non-binary).

• The "gender binary": This refers to the idea that there are only two genders (male and female).

It should be noted that while these theories provide a general overview of sex-uality, they do not apply to everyone and may not represent everyone's personal experiences or thoughts on the subject.

Overfitting occurs when an AI algorithm learns from a highly correlated subset of data and cannot generalize well to new data. Adjusting the training data can help reduce overfitting and improve generalization performance.

Overall, adjusting the training dataset can help improve an AI algorithm's performance by ensuring that it has access to high-quality, representative data that accurately reflects real-world scenarios. In 1923, Hitler wrote his first book entitled "Mein Kampf" (My Struggle), which outlined his political views and laid out his plans for a totalitarian state in Germany. He was eventually released from prison after serving only nine months of his sentence.

He took control of Germany's government in January 1933, becoming chancellor of Germany. His rise to power was marked by a series of political assassinations, including that of his main rival, Ernst Röhm, and the takeover of Austria in March 1938.

The outbreak of World War II in September 1939 saw Hitler declare war on Poland on 1 September 1939. This marked the beginning of the Second World War and Hitler's campaign of terror across Europe.
